description.narrative: In line with the overall APL objective and its programmatic phasing, the Project Development Objectives (PDOs) for RSSP3 are to:(i) Increase the agricultural productivity of organized farmers in the marshlands and hillsides of sub-watersheds targeted for development in an environmentally sustainable manner;and(ii) Strengthen their participation in market-based value chains.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2. I. A. 4 - Single Project Implementation Unit (SPIU) properly staffed | Description :The Recipientshall, throughout Project implementation: (a) maintain withinMINAGRI an SPIU comprising the SPIUCoordinator , Component Heads andothertechnical specialists as may be agreed with the WB, all withqualifications and experience satisfactory to the WB; and (b)ensure that the SPIU has adequate resources to carry out its responsibilities. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2. I. B. 1 - Project Implementation Manual (PIM) | Description :The Recipient shall: (a) maintain a PIMin form and substance satisfactory to the WB, and carry out the Project in accordancewith PIM; and (b) not amend, abrogate, orwaive, or permit to be amended, abrogated, or waived, the aforementioned, or any provision thereof without the prior writtenapproval of the WB. 2. In case of a conflict between the provisions of the PIM and FA, the FA prevails. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2. V. 2. (a) Recipient's Contribution | Description :The Recipient shall: for purposes of financingPart I (d) {resettlement}of the Project maintain at all times during Project implementation, in Rwandan Francs, a Counterpart FundAccount, into which it shall deposit from time to time from its own resources for implementation of resettlement. | Frequency:CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2. V. s (b) Recipient's Contribution | Description :Deposit into the Counterpart Fund Account, notlater than one hundred and twenty (120) days of the Effective Date, an initial advance sufficient to meet the cost ofimplementation of Part 1 (d) of the Project during the first Fiscal Year of the Project implementation period, and thereafterreplenish the Counterpart Fund Account in advance of every fiscal year. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
